docs.text: i must say from the outset that i have never been much of a kurt russell fan .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: i've seen some of his films ( silkwood , backdraft , unlawful entry ) and while he gave adequate performances , i have never been impressed with his work .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: breakdown , then , is something of a surprise .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: russell gives a fine performance , as do most of the cast , one that is not upstaged by the action orchestrated in the second half of the film .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: to say that he holds the film together would not be completely true , but he does it no harm .

docs.text: russell plays jeff , one half of a married couple travelling with his wife amy ( kathleen quinlan ) cross country to san diego to start a new job and a new life .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: while journeying through the desert their car breaks down and , left helpless and stranded , jeff waves down a passing truck driver ( j . t .

docs.text: because of a nasty incident earlier with a couple of ruffians , jeff decides to stay with the car while amy gets help .

docs.text: that , it seems , is the last time jeff ( or anyone else ) sees her .

docs.text: breakdown has been compared to several movies : george sluizer's the vanishing ( the original , hopefully , not his appalling hollywood remake ) , steven spielberg's duel and any number of hitchcock films .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: as with these , breakdown does not , for the most part , stray down the conventional path of the american action-thriller .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: jeff does not become a gun-toting vigilante on the hunt for his wife , but instead becomes a scared , confused everyman who has no idea what the hell is going on .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: when we do find out what has happened to amy , it does come as a slight disappointment , if only because it's too early in the film ; i for one could have done with an extra twenty minutes or so of mystery and bewilderment , but this affects the film little .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: russell , as mentioned earlier , is very good in his role , and kathleen quinlan is nowhere near as annoying as she was in apollo 13 .

docs.text: the reason he makes such a great villain is that he actually looks like a real person , one anyone would be able to trust , which makes the plot that much more believable .
